                    "comment": "wesm commented on issue #2055: ARROW-2611: [Python] Fix Python 2 integer serialization\nURL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/2055#issuecomment-390219559\n \n \n   Looking at this late. This fix seems odd to me but I haven't looked closely enough at the nuances to judge for certain. \r\n   \r\n   Would it be possible to have only a single int64 array in the serialized representation and then convert back to either PyInt or PyLong depending on the size of the value? In Python 2 it seems like `int` would always be a safe type if the value fits. If this sounds reasonable perhaps we can open a JIRA to investigate further another time\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------\nThis is an automated message from the Apache Git Service.\nTo respond to the message, please log on GitHub and use the\nURL above to go to the specific comment.\n \nFor queries about this service, please contact Infrastructure at:\nusers@infra.apache.org\n",
