                    "comment": "pschafhalter commented on issue #2055: ARROW-2611: [Python] Fix Python 2 integer serialization\nURL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/2055#issuecomment-390354040\n \n \n   I think the discussion with @pitrou touched on this.\r\n   \r\n   The main issue with converting to PyInt or PyLong depending on the size of the value is that if I serialize a `long`, I expect to receive a `long` on deserialization. In Python 2, small values may have type `long`, e.g. `type(0L) == long`, but choosing PyInt or PyLong depending on the size of the value would deserialize `0L` as an `int`.\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------\nThis is an automated message from the Apache Git Service.\nTo respond to the message, please log on GitHub and use the\nURL above to go to the specific comment.\n \nFor queries about this service, please contact Infrastructure at:\nusers@infra.apache.org\n",
